Deployment (vscode to Git):
Step 1:
Create a folder, open the browser, and search for GitLab. Sign up for GitLab, open GitLab, and create the repository.




Step 2:
Create a new file to get a URL in the repository.



Hint :
The commit message is important because new changes will be recorded within it.


Step 3:
Open chrome to download the git. And click install.

Step 4:
Go to the command prompt , type the git and press enter. Enter the git config –global
user.name “Git login name” and git config –global user.email “Git login email”


Step 5:
Open the vs code, select the git folder and create the new (sfdx project with manifest). Connect your development org and press the (Shift+ctrl+P).Click the (Package .xml generator) and select your components.Use the cd “git repository name” code to (change the directory for local to git folder).



HINT: Retrieve the Package.xml(it’s to find any error shown before the push method).
Step 6:
If you see unadded files, use the command (git add .) to prepare the files for commit.


Step 7:
Next step to commit.(file ready for push in repository)
Git commit -m “YOUR COMMIT MESSAGE”

HINT :
● 	Next step is to push the files within a git repository.
● 	Commit message is important to push the components.
● 	Check your branch in Git and ensure it matches in VS Code.

Step 8:
Open your git repository and verify your codes.

 
